			<ns0:name>mcgra...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109286297231979736865/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For the standalone NaCl build as done on the NaCl buildbots, the only way that doing a gyp (cross-)build works for ARM today is using a pile of magic environment variables found in buildbot/buildbot_pnacl.sh:gyp-arm-build.

It's likely that the hairiest compiler options are not actually needed and --sysroot alone covers it, but that needs to be verified.

More importantly, just GYP_DEFINES=target_arch=arm really ought to take care of all this stuff by itself.  Then the regular bot script (buildbot_standard.py) could be used without --no-gyp for the non-pnacl ARM bots.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-11T21:33:24.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-11T21:19:09.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>New</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
